Module org.nasdanika.flow
Package org.nasdanika.flow

Interface Artifact

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Adaptable, EObject, Marked, Marked, ModelElement, NamedElement, Notifier, PackageElement<Artifact>, ParticipantResponsibility<Artifact>, ServiceProvider<Artifact>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArtifactImpl
    public interface Artifact
extends ParticipantResponsibility<Artifact>, ServiceProvider<Artifact>
    A representation of the model object 'Artifact'.

    The following features are supported:

    • Repositories
    • Repository Keys
    • Input For
    • Output For
    • Payload For
    • Response For
    • Used By
    • Responsibilities
    • Children
    • Outbound Relationships
    • Inbound Relationships
    • Partition
    • Style
    • Template Keys
    • Templates
    • Instances
    See Also:
    FlowPackage.getArtifact()

    • Method Detail

      • getRepositories

        EList<Resource> getRepositories()
        Returns the value of the 'Repositories' reference list. The list contents are of type Resource. Resources in which this artifact can be stored. E.g. source code artifact can be stored in Git resource, and jar artifact can be stored in Maven repository resource.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Repositories' reference list.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getArtifact_Repositories()

      • getRepositoryKeys

        EList<String> getRepositoryKeys()
        Returns the value of the 'Repository Keys' attribute list. The list contents are of type String. Keys of artifact's repositories relative to the containing package ``resources/`` reference.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Repository Keys' attribute list.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getArtifact_RepositoryKeys()

      • getInputFor

        EList<FlowElement<?>> getInputFor()
        Returns the value of the 'Input For' reference list. The list contents are of type FlowElement<?>. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Input Artifacts'. Flow elements which take this artifact as an input.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Input For' reference list.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getArtifact_InputFor(), FlowElement.getInputArtifacts()

        the value of the 'Output For' reference list.
        See Also:

        EList<Transition> getPayloadFor()
        Returns the value of the 'Payload For' reference list. The list contents are of type Transition. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Payload'. Transitions for which this artifact is a part of their payload. Derived opposite to Transition payload.

        the value of the 'Payload For' reference list.
        See Also:

      • getResponsibilities

        EList<ArtifactParticipantResponsibility> getResponsibilities()
        Returns the value of the 'Responsibilities' reference list. The list contents are of type ArtifactParticipantResponsibility. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Artifact'. Responsibilities for this artifact at a flow element level if different from the flow element responsibilities. E.g. a participant responsible for an activity may delegate work on some artifact to another participant. In this case the activity responsible becomes accountable for the artifact and the delegate participant becomes responsible.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Responsibilities' reference list.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getArtifact_Responsibilities(), ArtifactParticipantResponsibility.getArtifact()

      • getChildren

        EMap<String,​Artifact> getChildren()
        Returns the value of the 'Children' map. The key is of type String, and the value is of type Artifact, Artifacts can be organized into a hierarchy (Product Breakdown Structure).
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Children' map.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getArtifact_Children()

      • getOutboundRelationships

        EMap<String,​Relationship> getOutboundRelationships()
        Returns the value of the 'Outbound Relationships' map. The key is of type String, and the value is of type Relationship, Outbound relationships to other artifacts. Artifact relationships can be used for modeling composite artifacts, e.g. modular/distributed systems such as cloud applications.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Outbound Relationships' map.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getArtifact_OutboundRelationships()

        Returns:
        the value of the 'Inbound Relationships' reference list.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getArtifact_InboundRelationships(), Relationship.getTarget()

      • isPartition

        boolean isPartition()
        Returns the value of the 'Partition' attribute. If true, this composite artifact shall be displayed as a partition on the parent component diagram.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Partition' attribute.
        See Also:
        setPartition(boolean), FlowPackage.getArtifact_Partition()

      • getTemplates

        EList<Artifact> getTemplates()
        Returns the value of the 'Templates' reference list. The list contents are of type Artifact. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Instances'. Artifacts can be organized into an inheritance hierarchy using templates reference. Artifacts inherit visual representation of templates. E.g. there might be an artifact "Cloud Cache" with multiple instances in different cloud solutions.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Templates' reference list.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getArtifact_Templates(), getInstances()

      • getInstances

        EList<Artifact> getInstances()
        Returns the value of the 'Instances' reference list. The list contents are of type Artifact. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Templates'. Artifacts for which this artifact is a template. Derived opposite to templates.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Instances' reference list.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getArtifact_Instances(), getTemplates()
